{\an8}<i>Schnell! Schnell!</i>

33
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:29,670
{\an8}-(ringing)
-(Homer cheering)

34
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:30,966
{\an8}(groans)

35
00:01:31,049 --> 00:01:32,339
{\an8}Homer Simpson.

36
00:01:32,425 --> 00:01:34,675
{\an8}You are the most infuriating,

37
00:01:34,761 --> 00:01:38,681
{\an8}Netflix DVD-burglaring,
barbecue-not-putting-out...

38
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:39,595
{\an8}(hooting)

39
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:41,732
{\an8}...man I ever met!

40
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:43,480
{\an8}Hold that thought.

41
00:01:43,561 --> 00:01:45,481
{\an8}Oh!

42
00:01:45,563 --> 00:01:48,153
{\an8}That man is beyond
redemption.

43
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:50,323
{\an8}That might seem
to be true...

44
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:51,951
{\an8}I sense a "but"
coming, Reverend...

45
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:54,528
{\an8}HOMER:
Here comes the butt!

46
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:58,374
{\an8}But I think you're up
to the challenge, Ned.

47
00:01:58,451 --> 00:02:00,701
{\an8}Oh, Reverend, I've been working
my Bible to the bone

48
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,117
{\an8}trying to save that man.

49
00:02:02,205 --> 00:02:04,745
{\an8}You know, Ned, God has never
given up on anyone.

50
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,293
{\an8}What about Sodom
and Gomorrah?

51
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:08,166
{\an8}He lovingly
destroyed them.

52
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:10,673
{\an8}Instead of
pushing Homer away,

53
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:14,545
{\an8}can't you find a way
to reach out and bring him in?

54
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:24,805
{\an8}(chanting)

55
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:26,308
(sighs)

56
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:34,695
Homer?

57
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:35,819
{\an8}(clears throat)

58
00:02:35,905 --> 00:02:37,195
{\an8}You know, our Bible study group

59
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:41,622
{\an8}is going
to the Holy Land next month.

60
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:43,793
{\an8}I'd like you and your family
to come as my guests.

61
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:45,462
Hmm, let me think...

62
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:47,880
Take my family to a war zone

63
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:50,749
on a bus filled
with religious lame-os

64
00:02:50,837 --> 00:02:53,167
in a country with no pork

65
00:02:53,256 --> 00:02:57,086
in a desert with no casinos...

66
00:02:57,177 --> 00:03:01,807
Ooh, where do I sign up?

67
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:04,730
Homer, I can hear your sarcasm
from inside the house.

68
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:06,559
And the dishwasher's on!

69
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:07,944
What's going on here?

70
00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:10,021
Mr. Flanders
invited us to Israel.

71
00:03:10,106 --> 00:03:11,896
I think he wants
to get Dad into Heaven.

72
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:14,573
-Great. More hell for me.
-(Bart and Homer laugh)

73
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:18,452
Ned Flanders, you would take
our family to the Holy Land

74
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:21,161
just to try to make my husband
a better man?

75
00:03:21,242 --> 00:03:24,622
Yep. I also want to try
something called "pita bread."

76
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:26,874
Well, we will take you up
on your offer.

77
00:03:26,956 --> 00:03:27,916
Oh...

78
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:29,879
But we insist on
paying our own way.

79
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:31,169
Oh!

80
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:33,002
And Homer, put
on some pants.

81
00:03:33,087 --> 00:03:35,047
(screaming)
Oh!

82
00:03:35,131 --> 00:03:38,131
The man hates pants.

83
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:48,024
♪♪

84
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:49,478
(glass shatters)

85
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,151
ALL:
<i>L'chaim!</i>

86
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:54,815
Homie, just tell them
what they want to hear.

87
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:56,111
I can't!

88
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:58,454
Latkes aren't as good
as American pancakes.

89
00:03:58,529 --> 00:03:59,409
(groans)

90
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:01,199
They're okay with applesauce.

91
00:04:01,282 --> 00:04:02,492
True enough.

92
00:04:04,285 --> 00:04:06,195
(grunts)

93
00:04:06,287 --> 00:04:09,997
A truckload of applesauce!
Eh...

94
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:16,132
Krusty, I've been
meaning to ask.

95
00:04:16,214 --> 00:04:18,054
What are you doing
on this tour?

96
00:04:18,132 --> 00:04:20,552
I believe that every Jew
should make a pilgrimage

97
00:04:20,635 --> 00:04:22,635
to Israel before he dies.

98
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,010
Yes, it is fitting.

99
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:25,267
(laughs)

100
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:26,808
Don't want to end up in hell.

101
00:04:26,891 --> 00:04:27,931
Jews don't
believe in hell.

102
00:04:28,017 --> 00:04:29,017
No hell?

103
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:31,152
Thank you, kid.
You made my day.

104
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:38,318
(vocalizing)

105
00:04:38,403 --> 00:04:40,243
(fiddle playing)

106
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:46,155
You're being paid
to clean the gutters!

107
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,825
This country's so historic.

108
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:55,587
For all we know, Jesus
could have given a talk

109
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:57,710
in Conference Room C.

110
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,717
MAN:
Welcome, welcome!

111
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:00,879
-Hey.
-Hey.

112
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:02,297
My name is Jacob.

113
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:06,055
You may notice I speak the
English with a slight accent.

114
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:08,179
This is because, as you
have probably guessed,

115
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:09,926
I used to live in London,

116
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:13,098
and that is why I sound
like Hugh Grant.

117
00:05:13,187 --> 00:05:14,807
Come on. Let's go.

118
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:16,687
We've got a lot of holy
sites to see. Yallah!

119
00:05:16,774 --> 00:05:17,984
We finish early,

120
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:20,107
we go to jewelry store
owned by my cousins.

121
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:21,454
(all laughing)

122
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:23,199
No joke. Is true.
Great prices.

123
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:25,581
You got to haggle. Otherwise
they don't respect you!

124
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:26,778
Come on. Let's go!

125
00:05:26,868 --> 00:05:28,488
Do you have any safety tips?

126
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:29,828
What are you talking about?

127
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:32,042
Israel is the safest country
in the world.

128
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:34,583
The only danger here
is dehydration.

129
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:36,667
Drink water.
Don't die. Looks bad on me.

130
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,503
Come on. Shut your face.
Let's go.

131
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:40,338
But it says here
in the brochure...

132
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,053
Brochure? Brochure?

133
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,143
Brochure?
Who wrote your brochure?

134
00:05:44,218 --> 00:05:46,638
The same schmuck
who wrote the New Testament?

135
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:47,971
I can't talk to you.

136
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:49,516
You talk to my
niece, Doreet.

137
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:51,179
Doreet, talk
to the stupids.

138
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,597
Shalom, goyim!

139
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:53,935
Shalom to you!

140
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:57,480
Shalom is the "aloha"
of this place.

141
00:05:57,565 --> 00:05:59,225
Okay, okay, lady.
You done talking now?

142
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:01,937
Who is licensed tour guide here,
you or me?

143
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:03,988
Now, everybody, we have
no time to see Masada.

144
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:06,412
Everybody died
there for nothing.

145
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:08,121
Okay, first stop:
Old City.

146
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:10,201
Come on. Let's go.
Please, shut your face!

147
00:06:10,286 --> 00:06:12,036
(gasps):
The Old City.

148
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:14,621
Where B.C. turned
into A.D.! Let's go!

149
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:17,127
Flanders, that stuff's been here
for thousands of years.

150
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:19,250
But the breakfast buffet
at this hotel,

151
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:21,167
which is included
in our package,

152
00:06:21,255 --> 00:06:22,715
closes in ten minutes!

153
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:25,049
Homer, that's not
why we're here.

154
00:06:25,134 --> 00:06:27,014
We can see the stations
of the cross.

155
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:30,055
After we see the stations
of the omelet bar.

156
00:06:30,139 --> 00:06:31,099
(groans)

157
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:33,732
Okay, let's just
put it to a vote.

158
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:37,403
I can't believe
we lost, Reverend.

159
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:39,070
Mm-hmm.

160
00:06:39,148 --> 00:06:40,818
These blueberry
muffins are bigger

161
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,360
than the ones we
had at Pechanga.

162
00:06:42,443 --> 00:06:45,113
Finally, something you like
better than Pechanga.

163
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:49,452
♪♪

164
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:52,164
Okay, everybody. Please
shut your face. Here we go.

165
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:55,575
This sacred spot on Mount Zion
is King David's tomb.

166
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:57,245
Also, where your Jesus,

167
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,423
who was a native-born Israeli,
by the way--

168
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:00,672
sandals, circumcised,

169
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:02,803
perfect English accent,
the whole deal...

170
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:05,090
This is where
he had his last supper

171
00:07:05,174 --> 00:07:06,684
before they took him away

172
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:08,549
and hammered him up
on that cross.

173
00:07:08,636 --> 00:07:09,756
(laughing)

174
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:12,426
Hey, you. You're not part
of the group. No listening!

175
00:07:12,515 --> 00:07:14,885
What? Is Israel.
Is free country.

176
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:20,186
(yelling in Hebrew)

177
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:21,273
(bleep)

178
00:07:21,357 --> 00:07:28,317
(continues yelling in Hebrew)

179
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:31,695
(bleep)

180
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:33,450
Okay, that's it.

181
00:07:33,536 --> 00:07:36,036
Because of him,
no Armenian quarter.

182
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:37,212
Forget it. It's gone.

183
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:40,210
All thanks to
Mr. Listen-for-Free.

184
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:42,213
Lord, please help Homer

185
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:46,625
experience the redemptive power
of this sacred land.

186
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:48,126
(gasps) He's going
for the record.

187
00:07:48,217 --> 00:07:49,427
He's going
for the record!

188
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:52,177
(groans)

189
00:07:52,263 --> 00:07:54,523
Flanders, you're not supposed
to help him.

190
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,729
Yeah, thanks a lot, Flanders.

191
00:07:56,809 --> 00:07:58,189
(sighs)

192
00:07:58,269 --> 00:08:00,189
Homer, do you think
you could show

193
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:02,691
just the slightest bit
of reverence?

194
00:08:02,773 --> 00:08:04,863
Ned, I'm an
American tourist.

195
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:08,032
I'm just here to see some
sights, try goofy new food

196
00:08:08,112 --> 00:08:11,912
and spread some shekels with my
Carolina Panthers credit card.

197
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:13,411
Panthers!

198
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:16,333
(sighs) Homer, could you at
least turn the camera off?

199
00:08:16,412 --> 00:08:19,582
If you say it
like Dracula, I will.

200
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:21,665
-Homer...
-Please, please, please...

201
00:08:21,751 --> 00:08:23,041
Bleh!

202
00:08:23,127 --> 00:08:24,087
(laughing)

203
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,960
That is going right
on StupidFlanders.org.

204
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:29,718
You know, Homer,
you might really benefit

205
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:33,510
from opening your heart to
the spirituality of this place.

206
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,056
Please, neighbor?

207
00:08:35,139 --> 00:08:36,929
This really means
a lot to you, huh?

208
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:39,516
Yes, but it
means more to you.

209
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:41,852
Boy, are you lousy
at reading minds.

210
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:43,148
Okay, okay.

211
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:44,771
For you, I'll try.

212
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:49,900
<i>FLANDERS:</i>
<i>Lord, I think I may</i>
<i>have finally reached him.</i>

213
00:08:51,614 --> 00:08:54,454
<i>FLANDERS (on recording):</i>
<i>Bleh! Bleh! Bleh!</i>

214
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:55,914
Homer, quit
playing that back.

215
00:08:55,993 --> 00:08:58,453
I'm not. It's
my ring tone.

216
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,078
Yello.
This is he.

217
00:09:00,164 --> 00:09:01,374
Yeah, I wanted to know:

218
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:03,957
do you deliver falafels
to the top of Mount Zion?

219
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:06,093
Great. I'd like
a large falafel

220
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:08,340
with pepperoni, sausage,
and extra cheese.

221
00:09:08,422 --> 00:09:10,722
Yes, I know
what a falafel is.

222
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:11,800
(sighs)

223
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:18,724
This, eh... Everybody,
look at my face.

224
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:22,018
This is the Western, or
as you say, Wailing Wall.

225
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:24,863
It is believed that the Lord
will grant the prayers

226
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:26,269
that are stuck into the cracks.

227
00:09:26,357 --> 00:09:29,647
Please, no graffiti,
no making the pishen. Yallah.

228
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:32,815
"Dear Lord: please fix the
following parking tickets:

229
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:35,525
A647253,

230
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:39,196
SP90325,

231
00:09:39,287 --> 00:09:42,617
Shelbyville 932871..."

232
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:47,380
Sad.

233
00:09:47,461 --> 00:09:49,381
Never gonna happen.

234
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:50,973
Sad.

235
00:09:51,048 --> 00:09:52,718
Maybe, if you were Brad Pitt.

236
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,300
Hey, boy, we're supposed
to be acting religiousy.

237
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:56,005
What are you up to?

238
00:09:56,095 --> 00:09:58,715
Reading prayers and
ignoring them, just like God.

239
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:00,676
Hey, this one's from you.

240
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:02,436
"Dear Lord,
don't let Marge find out

241
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:05,728
the hotel leaves chocolates
on the pillows at night."

242
00:10:05,813 --> 00:10:07,193
Why, you little...

243
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:09,693
(choking)

244
00:10:09,775 --> 00:10:11,565
"Give my dad
another heart attack?"

245
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:14,992
(shouts)

246
00:10:19,994 --> 00:10:22,544
Smite him like
the firstborn of Egypt.

247
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:26,172
Dead baby, dead baby, Passover,
dead baby, dead baby...

248
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:31,920
(chicken clucks)

249
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:51,940
(man crying prayer call)

250
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:53,816
Hey, why am I
running from a girl?

251
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:56,243
Call me when you're old enough
for your bat mitzvah.

