of the tomb of your Lord.

285
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:02,220
Or as he's known here,
"the man in the underpants."

286
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:03,564
Beautiful <i>tachtoonim.</i>

287
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:04,809
Oh, and what abs!

288
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:06,480
He was a real good-looking one.

289
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:08,979
Nice hair. Conditioner?
I think so.

290
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:10,901
And, Lord, thank you
for letting me see

291
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:13,570
this wonderful place
where the end of the world

292
00:12:13,649 --> 00:12:15,359
will soon begin.

293
00:12:15,443 --> 00:12:17,783
And thank you again for
the challenge of Homer Simpson.

294
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:19,702
We've all got
our crosses to bear.

295
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:22,370
Me Homer, you... the cross.

296
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:24,700
And now, let me gaze
with reverence

297
00:12:24,785 --> 00:12:26,245
upon the holy
resting place that...

298
00:12:26,328 --> 00:12:27,578
-(snoring)
-(yells)

299
00:12:27,663 --> 00:12:29,123
(mutters):
Uh, wha...?

300
00:12:29,206 --> 00:12:31,916
Homer, this is the
most sacred spot

301
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:34,501
in Christendom, not
your backyard hammock!

302
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:35,957
I'm sorry.

303
00:12:36,046 --> 00:12:38,666
It's just that these tours
are so exhausting.

304
00:12:38,758 --> 00:12:41,588
You're jet-lagged.
You're walking around all day.

305
00:12:41,677 --> 00:12:44,097
It's so hard to sleep
knowing Marge and the kids

306
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:46,390
