345
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:08,095
HOMER:
Ned! Ned, wait up!

346
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:13,347
Ned!
(gasps)

347
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:16,942
Ned's run off into the desert!

348
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:17,942
Aha!

349
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:21,573
A sand horse--
car of the desert!

350
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:31,747
(camel grunting)

351
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:37,461
Mmm!

352
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:39,553
Nothing like a tall glass
of lukewarm water

353
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:42,668
-to Jekyll down this Hyde.
-(wind whooshing)

354
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:44,626
Ooh, looks like
a sandstorm's brewing.

355
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:47,087
I'll just wait it out
at a movie.

356
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:51,681
Orthobot Prime,

357
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:54,225
the battle begins!

358
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:57,400
Not so fast--
we can't transform
on the Sabbath!

359
00:14:57,479 --> 00:15:01,229
Let us power down
and contemplate the Torah.

360
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:03,777
(mechanical whirring)

361
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:06,531
(robots praying)

362
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:12,198
(orchestral theme from
<i>Lawrence of Arabia </i>playing)

363
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:14,366
Flanders!

364
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:16,535
Stupid Flanders!

365
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,210
(wind whooshing)

366
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:22,004
(grunting, spitting)

367
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:24,967
Oh! There's sand
in my shoe! Ooh!

368
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:29,216
(relieved sighs):
Oh! Oh...!

369
00:15:29,303 --> 00:15:31,683
(camel grunting)

370
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:34,934
Good luck surviving without me!

371
00:15:35,017 --> 00:15:37,477
(to <i>Lawrence of Arabia </i>theme):
<i>♪ Thirsty ♪</i>

372
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:40,611
<i>♪ I am so thirsty ♪</i>

373
00:15:40,689 --> 00:15:44,689
<i>♪ And hungry and horny ♪</i>

374
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:49,197
<i>♪ But mostly just thirsty ♪</i>

375
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:53,291
<i>♪ I am so thirsty ♪</i>

376
00:15:53,369 --> 00:15:54,159
Huh?

377
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:55,664
(gasps):
Water!

378
00:15:58,165 --> 00:16:00,285
(hoarsely):
Oh! So salty!

379
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:03,626
Maybe if I add a little salt.

380
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:09,840
(dramatic music plays)

381
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:13,467
(choir vocalizing)

382
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:17,225
-(thunder rumbling)
-(wind whistling)

383
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:21,109
(choir vocalizing)

384
00:16:21,188 --> 00:16:23,398
(sobbing)

385
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:29,452
(sobbing loudly)

386
00:16:31,865 --> 00:16:33,825
You have been chosen, Homer.

387
00:16:33,909 --> 00:16:36,329
Chosen for what,
O mighty gherkin?

388
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:39,292
Rise and listen, my child.

389
00:16:39,373 --> 00:16:41,463
Yours is
a great destiny.

390
00:16:43,293 --> 00:16:44,803
Pickle, carrot, tomato, pickle,

391
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:45,918
carrot, tomato, pickle, carrot,

392
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:47,915
tomato, pickle,
carrot, tomato...

393
00:16:49,925 --> 00:16:52,635
Oh, Homie,
you're alive!

394
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:55,812
I am more than alive, woman.

395
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:58,019
I am the Chosen One

396
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,850
who shall unite all the faiths
of the Holy Land!

397
00:17:00,936 --> 00:17:04,146
I am... the Messiah!

398
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:06,231
But you still have
our passports, right?

399
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,031
Oh, yeah.

400
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,990
Gotta keep track of those.

401
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:12,030
(shouts):
The Messiah...

402
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:14,244
(normal voice):
has the passports.

403
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:21,617
-Dad, are you okay?
-I am more than okay!

404
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:24,457
I am the Messiah,
come to save the world!

405
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,253
Look upon me and shudder!

406
00:17:26,336 --> 00:17:27,456
I already do that.

407
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:29,586
Uh... Messiah?

408
00:17:29,673 --> 00:17:32,553
-Do you mind if I have
a word with your wife?
-As you wish.

409
00:17:32,634 --> 00:17:34,514
But look not
upon her with lust,

410
00:17:34,595 --> 00:17:36,425
and do not send her
friendly e-mails.

411
00:17:36,513 --> 00:17:38,023
That's how it begins.

412
00:17:38,098 --> 00:17:39,098
(nervous chuckle)

413
00:17:40,851 --> 00:17:42,851
Homer is suffering
from what's called

414
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:44,226
"Jerusalem syndrome."

415
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:46,483
Ah, yes, Jerusalem syndrome:

416
00:17:46,565 --> 00:17:49,775
the name given to religious
delusions or psychoses

417
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:51,860
that occur when
people visit Jerusalem.

418
00:17:51,945 --> 00:17:53,945
Have you ever noticed that
Dad always gets the disease

419
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:56,081
they write about in the
in-flight magazine?

420
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:57,198
MARGE:
Oh, my God!

421
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:58,544
Homer's gone!

422
00:17:59,703 --> 00:18:01,163
(groans)

423
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:02,656
What's he gonna do now?

424
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:06,708
Hmm, Dad said he was going
to unite all faiths.

425
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:10,554
And only one site is sacred
to Muslims, Christians and Jews:

426
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:11,721
The Dome of the Rock!

427
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:13,089
Dome of the Rock?

428
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:15,215
Messiah away...!

429
00:18:15,302 --> 00:18:16,852
(grunts)

430
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:20,309
(gasps):
This one says
"Carolina Panthers"!

431
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:22,560
Messiah says "Rowrr!"

432
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:26,154
{\an8}JACOB:
(speaks Hebrew)
Okay, everybody, come on.

433
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:28,020
This shrine contains the rock

434
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:30,817
on which Abraham was going
to sacrifice his son.

435
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:33,201
And Muslims believe
something, too.

436
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:35,198
To find out, hire
a Muslim tour guide.

437
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,700
<i>That's </i>a barrel
of laughs.

438
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,492
-Anyway, shut your face.
-Thanks, thanks.

439
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:40,325
You can stop
giving the tour now.

440
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:43,250
You don't want to
do a photo with me?
You can hold my gun.

441
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:47,250
-I used it in Entebbe.
I killed three Ugandans.
-No, thanks.

442
00:18:47,334 --> 00:18:48,384
Before you go in,

443
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:49,630
you fill out
comment card.

444
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:51,001
(groans):
Okay.

445
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:55,510
Uh, eh, don't
forget the back.

446
00:18:55,592 --> 00:18:57,182
You people are so pushy.

447
00:18:57,261 --> 00:18:59,101
What, Israeli
people are pushy?

448
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:01,559
How about you experience
a couple of genocides

449
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,310
and see how laid-back
<i>you </i>are?

450
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:06,232
We were purged from Spain!
Throw out of there!

451
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,981
They allow everybody in Spain!

452
00:19:08,063 --> 00:19:10,613
But for us, Jews,
no flamenco, get out!

453
00:19:10,691 --> 00:19:12,731
I'm pushy? Please.

454
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:13,988
You stay there,

455
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:16,609
surrounded by your
great enemy, Canada!

456
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:19,907
Try Syria for two months,
then we'll see who's pushy!

457
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:25,540
Attention, Christians,
Muslims, <i>and </i>Jews:

458
00:19:25,622 --> 00:19:28,332
I have come to gather you
into a new faith.

459
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:30,287
From now on,
you shall be called...

460
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:32,167
Chris-mu-jews.

461
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:34,344
-(unenthusiastic murmuring)
-MAN: I-I don't know.

462
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:38,223
Because when you get down to it,
aren't all religions the same?

463
00:19:38,302 --> 00:19:40,262
They tell you
what to eat,

464
00:19:40,345 --> 00:19:41,555
when to pray,

465
00:19:41,638 --> 00:19:44,058
how this imperfect clay
that we call man

466
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:46,941
can mold itself
to resemble the divine.

467
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:49,229
But we can never attain
that ultimate grace

468
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:52,023
while there is hatred in
our hearts for each other.

469
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:53,277
(quietly):
I did it.

470
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:54,228
I reached him.

471
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:56,198
Celebrate your commonality.

472
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:58,358
Some of us don't eat pork.

473
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:00,317
Some of us don't eat shellfish.

474
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:02,987
But all of us love chicken.

475
00:20:03,076 --> 00:20:04,616
-(excited murmuring)
-MAN: He's right!

476
00:20:04,703 --> 00:20:06,503
You can simmer
it in a <i>tagine.</i>

477
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:08,080
In a soup, you can boil it!

478
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:09,455
Spread the word!

479
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:11,791
Peace and chicken.

480
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:14,207
CROWD:
Peace and chicken!

481
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:16,336
Don't listen to this fat idiot!

482
00:20:16,423 --> 00:20:17,883
<i>I </i>am your Messiah!

483
00:20:17,966 --> 00:20:20,836
Avert your eyes
from my wrinkly arms!

484
00:20:20,928 --> 00:20:23,718
Uh-oh. Got another case
of Jerusalem syndrome.

485
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:26,225
This looks like a job for...

486
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:27,478
the Messiah!

487
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:28,893
(sighs)

488
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:30,853
(overlapping chatter)

489
00:20:33,148 --> 00:20:34,108
I want the window seat!

490
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:35,781
Krav maga!

491
00:20:35,859 --> 00:20:37,439
You can't hurt
what's already dead.

492
00:20:37,527 --> 00:20:39,317
-(grunts)
-(groans): I guess you can.

493
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:41,574
Homer, my friend, of all
the false messiahs today,

494
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:43,527
I think you came
closest to the truth.

495
00:20:43,617 --> 00:20:45,407
Well, if I made
any sense today,

496
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:48,584
it's because all the stuff
you've told me all these years

497
00:20:48,664 --> 00:20:50,464
has finally seeped in.

498
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:52,790
Can I buy you
a $12 turkey sandwich?

499
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:54,416
I'd like that.

500
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:56,343
How about a Greg Norman
Executive Putter

501
00:20:56,421 --> 00:20:58,631
-from the <i>SkyMall?</i>
-You'd probably
get a better deal

502
00:20:58,715 --> 00:20:59,965
